Pronunciation:
Notes: see also "pataka" North Island in Maori contexts of Maori <i>whata, </i> with spg variously <i>wata, wata[a2-acute], watta[as-acute], wutter,</i> etc. indicating anglicised pron. of [wata], [w t ], but not (as whare) [w t ]
